  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why is OTG not working properly for hard disk on Android Nougat?",
  "response": "If your OTG (On-The-Go) connection is not working properly for a hard disk on Android Nougat, there could be several potential reasons. Here are some common issues and troubleshooting steps:\n\n1. **Power Requirements**: Hard disks typically require more power than flash drives. Your smartphone may not be providing sufficient power through the OTG cable to the hard disk. Consider using a powered OTG hub or a hard disk with its own power source.\n\n2. **File System Compatibility**: Ensure that the hard disk is formatted in a compatible file system. Android devices typically support FAT32 and exFAT out of the box. NTFS or other file systems may not be recognized without additional software or drivers.\n\n3. **OTG Cable or Adapter**: The OTG cable or adapter itself could be faulty. Try using a different OTG cable or adapter to rule out this possibility.\n\n4. **Device Support**: Not all Android devices support OTG functionality. Verify that your specific device supports OTG and that it is enabled. You can check the device specifications or look for the OTG option in the settings.\n\n5. **Software Issues**: There could be software or firmware issues with your Android Nougat device. Ensure your device is up-to-date with the latest software updates. Sometimes drivers or patches are included in updates that improve hardware compatibility.\n\n6. **App Requirements**: Certain file management apps might be required to access external hard drives. Try using different file manager apps from the Google Play Store that specifically mention OTG support.\n\n7. **USB Debugging**: Enabling USB debugging in developer options may sometimes help resolve connectivity issues. Go to Settings > Developer Options > USB Debugging and enable it.\n\n8. **Permissions**: Ensure that the connected device is granted the necessary permissions for access. Check notification area or storage settings for permission prompts.\n\nIf after trying these steps the problem persists, it may be worth consulting the manufacturer's support for more specific troubleshooting or considering using the hard disk with a different device.",
